From 2ea48c264142cbe7abf4ebe361d6ec9469546eff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:56:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add waveshaping distortion stage (milestone 2)

Introduce the first non-linear distortion stage so the synth can actually
produce a hard kick instead of a pure sine.

- New dsp/distortion module: Soft (tanh), Hard (clip) and Fold (wavefolder)
  shapers, plus a one-pole DC blocker for the offset asymmetric shaping adds.
- New params: Shaper, Drive, Bias and Dist mix. Defaults (Soft, drive 0.0)
  preserve the milestone-1 clean-sine sound.
- Wire shaping into the process loop before the amplitude envelope, with a
  final safety clip on the output.
- Add a SHAPING section to the editor and make the waveform preview reflect
  the distortion settings.
- Document the milestone in docs/design/step2.distortion.md.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01GwURq9bT1AzMqUHKVyWkmv
